text:
The Cabinet of Ministers wants the Tax and Customs Services to have the status of a single legal entity

06 Nov 2019, 17:10


The Cabinet of Ministers approved a bill according to which the State Tax and State Customs Services will have the status of a single legal entity. Now the regional divisions of these bodies have their own separate legal entities.

According to the press service of the government, the bill "On Amending the Tax Code of Ukraine and some other legislative acts of Ukraine on improving the governance structure in the field of state tax and customs policy", which was approved by the Cabinet, introduces a new format for the activities of the State Customs Service and the State Customs Service as a single legal persons, in connection with which their territorial bodies will carry out activities not as legal entities of public law, but as separate divisions.
It is also noted that he must solve one of the key issues necessary for reforming tax authorities, namely, the introduction of an effective organizational structure in them, built on a functional principle.
In particular, amendments will be made to the Tax Code of Ukraine, the laws of Ukraine "On Central Executive Bodies" and "On Public Service", according to which:
- the list of authorities that will have the status of a controlling body is being clarified, a clear delineation of their functions in the field of administration of taxes and fees is established;
- The status of the state tax inspectorates as structural units of the territorial bodies (separate units) of the State Tax Administration is fixed;
- details are provided regarding the delegation of authority to perform the functions provided for by the Tax Code, legislation on the payment of ERUs, in the leading vertical of the SPSU;
- clarifications are made: of the levels of regulatory bodies for the possibility of administrative appeal of decisions of such bodies by taxpayers; features of accounting for large taxpayers in the territorial (separate subdivision) of the State Tax Service of Ukraine, which provides support for large taxpayers, or its structural divisions; Codex terminology regarding the names of authorities implementing tax and customs policies;
- The features of remuneration and service by state employees of the State Customs Service and the State Customs Service and their territorial bodies were determined.
Earlier it was reported that the Cabinet of Ministers postponed the date of entry into force of the decree prohibiting the import into the territory of Ukraine of railway cars produced in Russia.


